        <div class="interactive-demo">
            <h2>Interactive Examples</h2>
            <p>Try these JavaScript examples to see the language in action:</p>
            
            <div class="demo-container">
                <h3>String Manipulation</h3>
                <p>Enter text and see JavaScript transform it:</p>
                <input type="text" id="textInput" placeholder="Enter text here" value="Hello JavaScript!">
                <br>
                <button class="button" onclick="toUpperCase()">To Upper Case</button>
                <button class="button" onclick="toLowerCase()">To Lower Case</button>
                <button class="button" onclick="reverseText()">Reverse Text</button>
                <div class="output" id="stringOutput">Output will appear here</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="demo-container">
                <h3>Calculator</h3>
                <p>Perform basic calculations with JavaScript:</p>
                <input type="number" id="num1" placeholder="First number" value="10">
                <input type="number" id="num2" placeholder="Second number" value="5">
                <br>
                <button class="button" onclick="add()">Add</button>
                <button class="button" onclick="subtract()">Subtract</button>
                <button class="button" onclick="multiply()">Multiply</button>
                <button class="button" onclick="divide()">Divide</button>
                <div class="output" id="calcOutput">Result will appear here</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="demo-container">
                <h3>DOM Manipulation</h3>
                <p>Change the style and content of elements:</p>
                <button class="button" onclick="changeColor()">Change Color</button>
                <button class="button" onclick="changeText()">Change Text</button>
                <button class="button" onclick="toggleVisibility()">Toggle Visibility</button>
                <div class="output" id="domOutput">This element will be manipulated</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="demo-container">
                <h3>Array Operations</h3>
                <p>Working with arrays in JavaScript:</p>
                <button class="button" onclick="showArray()">Show Array</button>
                <button class="button" onclick="sortArray()">Sort Array</button>
                <button class="button" onclick="filterArray()">Filter Even Numbers</button>
                <button class="button" onclick="mapArray()">Double Values</button>
                <div class="output" id="arrayOutput">Array operations result will appear here</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="interactive-demo">
            <h2>JavaScript Code Example</h2>
            <p>Here's a sample JavaScript function that calculates the factorial of a number:</p>
            
            <div class="code-example">
                <pre><code>function factorial(n) {
    if (n === 0 || n === 1) {
        return 1;
    }
    return n * factorial(n - 1);
}

// Example usage
const number = 5;
console.log(`Factorial of ${number} is ${factorial(number)}`);
// Output: Factorial of 5 is 120</code></pre>
            </div>
            
            <div class="demo-container">
                <p>Try it yourself: Calculate the factorial of a number</p>
                <input type="number" id="factorialInput" placeholder="Enter a number" value="5" min="0" max="20">
                <button class="button" onclick="calculateFactorial()">Calculate Factorial</button>
                <div class="output" id="factorialOutput">Result will appear here</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
